  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: the boundary-condition dataset (dataset/bc-inlet-profiles) carries a dataVintage of 2024-11-08T00:00:00Z, which predates the model revision of 2024-11-29T00:00:00Z by approximately three weeks. The assessment narrative characterises the turbulence-model coefficient update introduced in that revision as 'not material to the inlet boundary profiles', but no formal re-validation against refreshed inlet data was performed.",
