      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties sourced from traceable measurements; uncertainty in key inputs propagated to QoI.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles derived from dataset bc-inlet-profiles (PIV-measured, dataVintage 2024-11-08). Blood analogue viscosity from dataset material-properties (rheometry, 2025-01-15). One-at-a-time sensitivity study shows ±5% variation in inlet profile magnitude produces < 2% change in RH. The model underwent a turbulence-model coefficient update on 2024-11-29; the assessment team judged this revision immaterial to the inlet boundary-condition dataset because the profiles are kinematically derived and independent of turbulence closure. No formal re-validation against post-revision inlet data was conducted. Input uncertainty propagation otherwise complete; Gradation 2 achieved."
